SYDNEY - The 39th Annual Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras parade boasted drag queens, dancers and police officers.A couple take a selfie during the annual Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras festival in Sydney, Australia 4 March, 2017The Mardi Gras began as a protest in 1978, but police cracked down heavily on marchers and more than 50 were arrested in the brief riot which followed.A participant in the annual Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras wears a giant heart with the word equality in Sydney, Australia 4 March, 2017.However, the event helped bring legislative change, including the decriminalisation of homosexuality in New South Wales in 1984.A participant wears elaborate make-up and headdress during the annual Sydney Gay and Lesbian Mardi Gras festival in Sydney, Australia 4 March 2017.Police now take part in the march, as do the Australian military with more than 100 Australian Defence Force members in the parade. Reuters